1
00:00:01,037 --> 00:00:02,7
Previously on Lucifer...

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:03,9
MAZE: You're the Lord of Hell,

3
00:00:04,013 --> 00:00:05,0
for crying out loud.

4
00:00:05,021 --> 00:00:07,2
Shouldn't you be spending
your valuable time

5
00:00:07,046 --> 00:00:09,5
doing something
more significant?

6
00:00:09,080 --> 00:00:12,3
I'm retired, Maze.
I've got nothing but time.

7
00:00:12,051 --> 00:00:14,8
Your return to the Underworld
has been requested.

8
00:00:15,010 --> 00:00:17,0
Remind Dad that I quit Hell

9
00:00:17,022 --> 00:00:19,5
because I was sick and tired
of playing a part in his play.

10
00:00:19,072 --> 00:00:21,5
We should be out there
solving a homicide

11
00:00:21,069 --> 00:00:23,4
and punishing
those responsible.

12
00:00:23,073 --> 00:00:25,3
We? How could you
possibly help me?

13
00:00:25,056 --> 00:00:27,0
I have the ability

14
00:00:27,023 --> 00:00:28,6
to draw out peoples'
forbidden desires.

15
00:00:28,090 --> 00:00:30,7
I got it. I got it.
The name,

16
00:00:30,094 --> 00:00:32,0
the whole Lucifer thing.

17
00:00:32,024 --> 00:00:33,9
And desire is like
your superpower.

18
00:00:34,020 --> 00:00:35,4
Mm, it's more like
a gift from God really.

19
00:00:35,062 --> 00:00:37,0
You're thinking
about it, aren't you?

20
00:00:37,024 --> 00:00:38,1
See, I wouldn't recommend it.

21
00:00:38,037 --> 00:00:39,3
I'm like walking heroin.

22
00:00:39,058 --> 00:00:41,0
Ah, you're the Devil. (laughs)

23
00:00:41,020 --> 00:00:42,4
Mm, correct.

24
00:00:42,062 --> 00:00:44,4
(gunshot, Chloe gasps)

25
00:00:47,009 --> 00:00:49,1
(gunshots, Lucifer grunting)

26
00:00:49,038 --> 00:00:51,2
Give me one second.

27
00:00:52,097 --> 00:00:55,0
Please. Please
don't kill me.

28
00:00:55,022 --> 00:00:56,1
You're gonna wish

29
00:00:56,039 --> 00:00:57,5
that's all I did to you.

30
00:00:57,076 --> 00:00:59,1
MAZE:
I just can't understand

31
00:00:59,035 --> 00:01:00,5
why you would save
a human life.

32
00:01:00,077 --> 00:01:02,2
Something different about her

33
00:01:02,043 --> 00:01:04,1
that I don't quite understand,
and it vexes me.

34
00:01:04,039 --> 00:01:05,8
Maybe it's not her
that's different.

35
00:01:06,006 --> 00:01:07,5
LUCIFER:
Right. Here's the deal.

36
00:01:07,073 --> 00:01:09,7
We can have as much
naked cuddle time as you desire,

37
00:01:09,094 --> 00:01:12,3
but you're gonna have
to listen to me, too.

38
00:01:12,057 --> 00:01:14,3
You know, just an existential
dilemma or two. Deal?

39
00:01:14,057 --> 00:01:16,2
LINDA:
Yes.

40
00:01:18,037 --> 00:01:20,1
♪♪

41
00:01:22,029 --> 00:01:26,8
♪ I ain't go no soul,
the preacher told me so ♪

42
00:01:27,008 --> 00:01:31,6
♪ I'm out... on my own ♪

43
00:01:31,088 --> 00:01:35,0
♪ I ain't got no soul,
the preacher told me so... ♪

44
00:01:35,026 --> 00:01:37,9
MAN:
Save your soul!
It's up to you!

45
00:01:38,018 --> 00:01:39,5
I ask you to repent!

46
00:01:39,076 --> 00:01:41,3
Repent your sins

47
00:01:41,060 --> 00:01:42,6
before it is too late!

48
00:01:42,081 --> 00:01:43,6
It is the end

49
00:01:43,081 --> 00:01:44,9
of times!

50
00:01:45,019 --> 00:01:46,8
The Devil walks among us!

51
00:01:47,002 --> 00:01:50,5
Padre, you have no idea how
right you are. (chuckles)

52
00:01:50,073 --> 00:01:52,0
But there's no need
to be angry about it.

53
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:53,4
Enjoy the ride.

54
00:01:53,061 --> 00:01:54,7
MAN:
Bless you.

55
00:01:54,099 --> 00:01:56,6
Have you seen the face
of the Devil?

56
00:01:56,086 --> 00:01:59,6
Oh, every morning
in the mirror, pal.

57
00:01:59,082 --> 00:02:00,9
Exactly!

58
00:02:01,012 --> 00:02:02,4
He's in all of us!

59
00:02:02,062 --> 00:02:04,5
In our every moment
of weakness.

60
00:02:04,070 --> 00:02:05,9
Look at this world!

61
00:02:06,016 --> 00:02:08,5
The sin, the lust!

62
00:02:08,079 --> 00:02:10,1
It is the Devil's touch.

63
00:02:10,034 --> 00:02:11,9
N-N-No, don't give me
credit for all that.

64
00:02:12,013 --> 00:02:14,2
You humans do plenty
all on your own.

65
00:02:14,046 --> 00:02:16,4
(microphone feedback squeals)

66
00:02:16,067 --> 00:02:17,8
(sighs)

67
00:02:19,059 --> 00:02:20,7
What's your problem, pal?

68
00:02:20,097 --> 00:02:22,7
Excuse me?

69
00:02:22,097 --> 00:02:24,6
Yeah, uh, why don't you move
your shtick along.

70
00:02:24,081 --> 00:02:26,4
Okay, I'm not sharing
my tips with you,

71
00:02:26,064 --> 00:02:28,4
- if that's what you're
angling for.
- Oh.

72
00:02:28,065 --> 00:02:30,4
Right. Is this
a performance?

73
00:02:30,061 --> 00:02:32,2
Are you like the Chewbacca and
the Spider-Man down the street?

74
00:02:32,048 --> 00:02:33,9
I have to say,
you're very good.

75
00:02:34,015 --> 00:02:35,5
Yeah, so why don't you
go bother them.

76
00:02:35,078 --> 00:02:36,7
You're bad for my business.

77
00:02:36,099 --> 00:02:39,6
Repent! The Devil...

78
00:02:39,086 --> 00:02:41,4
Isn't finished with you yet.

79
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:45,5
You see, what I hate
more than anything is a liar,

80
00:02:45,070 --> 00:02:49,5
a charlatan, someone who doesn't
believe in what they say.

81
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:52,2
So what are you gonna do
about it?

82
00:02:52,050 --> 00:02:55,0
Why, make you a believer,
of course.

83
00:02:57,067 --> 00:02:58,6
(screams)

84
00:02:58,088 --> 00:03:00,4
S-S... uh, stay away!

85
00:03:00,068 --> 00:03:01,7
He's the Devil!

86
00:03:01,093 --> 00:03:03,4
You don't understand!

87
00:03:03,064 --> 00:03:05,3
This isn't a performance!
He's the Devil!

88
00:03:05,056 --> 00:03:06,9
He's the Devil!
(crowd clamoring)

89
00:03:07,018 --> 00:03:08,8
It's true. It is true.
(applause)

90
00:03:11,098 --> 00:03:13,8
(chuckles)
Yes, thanks, everyone.

91
00:03:14,007 --> 00:03:16,9
I'm, uh, here till, well, the
end of time, actually. (laughs)

92
00:03:17,019 --> 00:03:18,7
LINDA: So you're the Devil.
LUCIFER: Yes.

93
00:03:18,099 --> 00:03:23,2
Yes. Well, Satan, Beelzebub,
Old Scratch.

94
00:03:23,045 --> 00:03:25,3
Actually, I like that one
in particular.

95
00:03:25,054 --> 00:03:27,6
But, uh, those were
the old me.

96
00:03:27,087 --> 00:03:29,6
These days, you just have
plain old Lucifer.

97
00:03:29,087 --> 00:03:33,3
And you've left Hell behind to
take a vacation in Los Angeles.

98
00:03:33,054 --> 00:03:35,0
Well, where else would I go?

99
00:03:36,088 --> 00:03:38,4
You don't seem too bothered

100
00:03:38,067 --> 00:03:40,3
by my being
the Prince of Darkness.

101
00:03:40,059 --> 00:03:43,1
I'm willing to work
within your metaphor.

102
00:03:43,034 --> 00:03:44,8
Right.

103
00:03:45,010 --> 00:03:46,8
Sometimes it's easier
to make intimate issues

104
00:03:47,010 --> 00:03:49,3
about something
bigger than yourself.

105
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:51,5
Well, there are few things
bigger than myself.

106
00:03:51,073 --> 00:03:53,8
I'm well aware.

107
00:03:54,006 --> 00:03:54,9
(chuckles)

108
00:03:55,011 --> 00:03:57,4
(sighs):
Ah.

109
00:03:57,061 --> 00:04:01,7
Last we spoke, you were bothered
about feelings of humanity.

110
00:04:01,099 --> 00:04:04,2
I was, yes, but I have good news
for you on that front.

111
00:04:04,045 --> 00:04:05,2
I'm healed.

112
00:04:05,045 --> 00:04:06,8
Is that so?

113
00:04:07,004 --> 00:04:08,9
Yes. Yes, back to my normal,
devilish self.

114
00:04:09,012 --> 00:04:10,5
No pesky empathy to be found.

115
00:04:10,071 --> 00:04:11,8
I'd kick a puppy

116
00:04:12,008 --> 00:04:13,3
if one waltzed by.

117
00:04:13,054 --> 00:04:15,3
I'm joking.
Puppies don't waltz.

118
00:04:15,059 --> 00:04:18,0
You like to hide insecurity
in humor,

119
00:04:18,025 --> 00:04:19,6
don't you?

120
00:04:19,084 --> 00:04:20,7
(laughs):
I don't have insecurities.

121
00:04:20,097 --> 00:04:23,0
Mm. Everyone does.

122
00:04:24,072 --> 00:04:27,8
(sighs) Very well.
I'll play your game.

123
00:04:28,001 --> 00:04:29,7
What do you think
I'm insecure about?

124
00:04:29,093 --> 00:04:32,2
That you are changing,

125
00:04:32,044 --> 00:04:34,5
but that you don't know
what's causing the change.

126
00:04:34,077 --> 00:04:36,3
Or who.

127
00:04:38,036 --> 00:04:40,3
We'll pick this up next time.

128
00:04:40,053 --> 00:04:42,2
What? Oh, very well.

129
00:04:42,049 --> 00:04:44,9
A deal's a deal.
Though, why do I feel

130
00:04:45,011 --> 00:04:46,9
like you're getting more
out of our bargain than I am?

131
00:04:47,012 --> 00:04:48,0
(gasps)
Ooh! Hello!

132
00:04:48,028 --> 00:04:50,4
Thank you. Here.

133
00:04:50,066 --> 00:04:52,9
- Donald.
- How are you, sir?

134
00:04:53,012 --> 00:04:56,2
♪ Hear voices through the wall ♪

135
00:04:56,050 --> 00:04:57,9
♪ Whole room
comes to their feet ♪

136
00:04:58,013 --> 00:05:00,0
♪ I know it's never enough ♪

137
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:01,8
♪ Rendered obsolete ♪

138
00:05:01,097 --> 00:05:03,6
♪ Just a shot in the dark ♪

139
00:05:03,084 --> 00:05:05,4
♪ My God, what have you done? ♪

140
00:05:05,064 --> 00:05:07,3
♪ Spills out into the streets ♪

141
00:05:07,055 --> 00:05:09,3
♪ All bows down to ♪

142
00:05:09,056 --> 00:05:11,1
♪ Valkyrie ♪

143
00:05:11,035 --> 00:05:14,9
♪ Tell me everything
and, baby, I'll believe ♪

144
00:05:15,014 --> 00:05:18,9
♪ Dancing with the Devil,
sweating gasoline ♪

145
00:05:19,015 --> 00:05:20,7
(camera clicks)
♪ Rolling down the river ♪

146
00:05:20,098 --> 00:05:22,1
♪ 'Cause it's automatic ♪

147
00:05:22,032 --> 00:05:23,3
(camera clicks)
♪ So dramatic ♪

148
00:05:23,057 --> 00:05:25,2
♪ Every time guaranteed... ♪

149
00:05:25,049 --> 00:05:26,6
Oh, I didn't order a drink.

150
00:05:26,082 --> 00:05:27,7
MAZE:
Courtesy of the owner.

151
00:05:27,099 --> 00:05:29,7
This is from Lucifer?

152
00:05:29,099 --> 00:05:32,2
He asked me to make you
something you'd like.

153
00:05:32,041 --> 00:05:33,5
Did I get it wrong?

154
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:36,2
You and Lucifer
seem really close.

155
00:05:36,050 --> 00:05:39,5
I followed him
through the gates of Hell.

156
00:05:39,079 --> 00:05:41,3
I'll take that as a "yes."

157
00:05:41,050 --> 00:05:42,6
(laughs)

158
00:05:46,059 --> 00:05:48,6
(piano playing gentle melody)

159
00:06:03,015 --> 00:06:05,2
(sighs)
Hello, Detective.

160
00:06:05,049 --> 00:06:07,7
How has your
undercover surveillance

161
00:06:07,091 --> 00:06:09,3
of my activities
gone so far?

162
00:06:09,053 --> 00:06:11,3
I've looked into you.

163
00:06:11,058 --> 00:06:13,8
Your name really is
Lucifer Morningstar.

164
00:06:14,004 --> 00:06:16,7
And as far as I can tell,
you didn't exist five years ago.

165
00:06:16,091 --> 00:06:18,1
On the earthly plane, no.

166
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:21,6
People don't appear
out of thin air.

167
00:06:21,088 --> 00:06:23,4
Who were you?

168
00:06:23,063 --> 00:06:26,5
How did you survive getting shot
six times by Jimmy Barnes?

169
00:06:26,072 --> 00:06:29,6
Is that your normal reaction
to someone saving your life?

170
00:06:29,084 --> 00:06:31,5
- Investigating them?
- When I see something

171
00:06:31,076 --> 00:06:33,6
I can't explain, yeah,
I look for answers.

172
00:06:33,081 --> 00:06:35,4
Well, I've given you the answer,
Detective. It's not my fault

173
00:06:35,068 --> 00:06:36,4
you won't accept it.

174
00:06:36,068 --> 00:06:37,4
Do you know what I think?

175
00:06:37,069 --> 00:06:39,3
I stopped trying to guess.

176
00:06:39,056 --> 00:06:41,1
I think you like me.

177
00:06:41,036 --> 00:06:43,9
What part of the look on my face
gives you that impression?

178
00:06:44,011 --> 00:06:45,9
No, no, no, it's not about
the face. It's about the eyes,

179
00:06:46,011 --> 00:06:47,8
what's behind them.
I think you see

180
00:06:48,003 --> 00:06:49,8
something that you truly desire,
and you...

181
00:06:50,003 --> 00:06:51,4
you don't know
what to do with yourself,

182
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:54,0
do you?

183
00:06:54,024 --> 00:06:55,8
Really?

184
00:06:56,008 --> 00:06:57,2
Uh-huh.

185
00:06:57,041 --> 00:06:58,5
- (chuckles)
- (laughs)

186
00:06:58,075 --> 00:07:00,5
- Hmm. (laughs)
- That's more like it.

187
00:07:00,075 --> 00:07:02,5
(sighs)

188
00:07:04,088 --> 00:07:07,0
Detective, I never knew
you cared. (chuckles)

189
00:07:07,026 --> 00:07:08,0
Mm.

190
00:07:08,026 --> 00:07:10,2
- Ooh.
- (laughing)

191
00:07:12,022 --> 00:07:13,8
(sighs)

192
00:07:16,006 --> 00:07:17,5
(both sigh)

193
00:07:17,077 --> 00:07:19,3
No bulletproof vest.

194
00:07:19,060 --> 00:07:20,9
What?

195
00:07:21,010 --> 00:07:22,5
I just couldn't imagine
how you'd get it

196
00:07:22,077 --> 00:07:24,2
under that suit,
but I had to check.

197
00:07:24,044 --> 00:07:26,2
What is it? What is it?
What is it?

198
00:07:26,044 --> 00:07:27,9
I'm gonna figure out
your secret, Lucifer.

199
00:07:28,019 --> 00:07:30,5
Not a secret if I'm
telling you the answer!

200
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:32,7
It's...

201
00:07:32,091 --> 00:07:34,8
Why don't I affect
you, Detective?

202
00:07:35,008 --> 00:07:36,7
What makes you
different?

203
00:07:36,095 --> 00:07:38,7
I guess we both
have our mysteries.

204
00:07:38,091 --> 00:07:41,4
Ah. Well, I'll show you mine
if you show me yours.

205
00:07:41,062 --> 00:07:42,7
(phone ringing)

206
00:07:42,096 --> 00:07:44,5
Oh, God, not
that again.

207
00:07:44,075 --> 00:07:46,5
Decker.

208
00:07:48,038 --> 00:07:49,5
Are you sure?

209
00:07:49,076 --> 00:07:51,0
Yes.

210
00:07:51,026 --> 00:07:53,1
Yes, um,
please send me the address.

211
00:07:53,034 --> 00:07:55,3
I... I owe you one.

212
00:07:55,047 --> 00:07:57,6
(sighs)
Oh, finally.

213
00:07:57,081 --> 00:07:59,6
Now that affected you.
What was it?

214
00:08:01,002 --> 00:08:02,4
Detective?

215
00:08:03,056 --> 00:08:05,3
Detective?!

216
00:08:08,023 --> 00:08:10,2
(indistinct police radio
chatter, camera clicking)

217
00:08:10,045 --> 00:08:12,2
Come on. Active scene.

218
00:08:18,045 --> 00:08:20,3
The victim was being
followed by a paparazzo.

219
00:08:20,058 --> 00:08:21,7
Tried to lose his tail.

220
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,4
Instead, lost
control of his car.

221
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:24,7
Died on impact.

222
00:08:24,096 --> 00:08:27,1
The paparazzo
following him was...?

223
00:08:27,034 --> 00:08:28,8
Was Nick Hofmeister, yeah.

224
00:08:29,005 --> 00:08:31,9
Who's the victim?

225
00:08:32,018 --> 00:08:33,6
Robbie Russell Jr.

226
00:08:33,084 --> 00:08:36,1
The son of the movie star?

227
00:08:36,035 --> 00:08:38,1
He wasn't
in the business, was he?

228
00:08:38,035 --> 00:08:40,1
Didn't stop everyone from
wanting pictures of him.

229
00:08:40,035 --> 00:08:42,3
They're vultures.

230
00:08:42,060 --> 00:08:44,0
You get a statement from Nick?

231
00:08:44,023 --> 00:08:45,6
You can't be involved
in an active case

232
00:08:45,090 --> 00:08:47,3
until you're off
medical leave.

233
00:08:47,057 --> 00:08:51,1
Listen, I get why you
wanted to be here, I do.

234
00:08:51,032 --> 00:08:53,2
But you have
to bring him?

235
00:08:58,095 --> 00:09:00,2
You've got to be kidding me.

236
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:01,3
What are you doing here?

237
00:09:01,054 --> 00:09:03,8
Oh! How's your ex?

238
00:09:04,008 --> 00:09:06,1
He's not the reason
you rushed over here, is he?

239
00:09:06,038 --> 00:09:07,6
Answer the question.

240
00:09:07,088 --> 00:09:09,3
I'm trying to solve
my mystery, Detective.

241
00:09:09,059 --> 00:09:12,1
If I don't affect you,
I'm curious as to what does.

242
00:09:13,063 --> 00:09:15,1
Oh, and I think

243
00:09:15,034 --> 00:09:16,6
I've just found my answer.

244
00:09:16,084 --> 00:09:18,0
Who's that?

245
00:09:18,022 --> 00:09:19,1
He's a paparazzo.

246
00:09:19,039 --> 00:09:21,2
Oh. Had a little
run-in with him

247
00:09:21,043 --> 00:09:23,8
during your Hot Tub High School
days, did you? Huh? Is that it?

248
00:09:24,002 --> 00:09:25,8
Yeah, you could say that.
He's a cockroach.

249
00:09:26,002 --> 00:09:28,1
But he'll figure a way
out of this. He always does.

250
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,8
You want to talk
to him, don't you?

251
00:09:30,007 --> 00:09:31,1
Well, go on, then.
What's stopping you?

252
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,1
The rules? Huh?

253
00:09:33,032 --> 00:09:34,4
Detective Douche?

254
00:09:34,061 --> 00:09:36,3
If you desire something,
just take it.

255
00:09:36,057 --> 00:09:38,4
CHLOE: Lucifer,
what are you doing?

256
00:09:38,062 --> 00:09:41,1
Hello.

257
00:09:41,037 --> 00:09:43,2
(grunts, groans)

258
00:09:43,050 --> 00:09:45,2
CHLOE:
You finally did it, Nick.

259
00:09:45,041 --> 00:09:47,3
You finally wanted a photo
so bad that you killed someone.

260
