Far be it for me

780
00:29:24,051 --> 00:29:26,1
to call someone's morality
into question, but...

781
00:29:26,034 --> 00:29:29,0
I believe that
photo was planned.

782
00:29:29,022 --> 00:29:31,6
Yeah.

783
00:29:31,089 --> 00:29:34,3
Makes me wonder
what else was.

784
00:29:36,048 --> 00:29:38,3
Look at this.

785
00:29:38,052 --> 00:29:39,8
Celebrity
shouting matches,

786
00:29:40,002 --> 00:29:41,2
fistfights.

787
00:29:41,044 --> 00:29:42,7
Josh had the first photo
on every one.

788
00:29:42,094 --> 00:29:44,1
It escalates.

789
00:29:44,036 --> 00:29:46,3
Overdose. Suicide.

790
00:29:46,053 --> 00:29:48,1
- Or so it appeared.
- Well, I suppose

791
00:29:48,032 --> 00:29:50,1
the best way to be first is
to know it'll happen beforehand.

792
00:29:50,033 --> 00:29:53,2
So he follows Robbie, intent on
running him off the road,

793
00:29:53,046 --> 00:29:56,4
but doesn't count on his own car
running off as well.

794
00:29:56,062 --> 00:29:58,3
This is cold,
premeditated murder.

795
00:29:58,054 --> 00:30:00,0
- Mm.
- Nick's a slimeball.

796
00:30:00,021 --> 00:30:02,1
I just... I don't think
he'd go this far.

797
00:30:02,034 --> 00:30:04,5
Which means Josh maybe
convinced him to take the fall.

798
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:05,7
The question is: why?

799
00:30:05,093 --> 00:30:07,3
Well, who cares?

800
00:30:07,051 --> 00:30:09,3
We know Josh is guilty.
Let's punish him.

801
00:30:09,051 --> 00:30:11,8
Ah, I could add an ironic twist,
like I used to when I ran Hell.

802
00:30:12,010 --> 00:30:13,6
Yeah, no,
it doesn't work that way,

803
00:30:13,089 --> 00:30:14,8
because I need evidence.

804
00:30:15,010 --> 00:30:16,8
LUCIFER:
Well, you have plenty.

805
00:30:17,006 --> 00:30:18,1
Circumstantial.

806
00:30:18,031 --> 00:30:19,4
I need concrete proof.
(sighs)

807
00:30:19,065 --> 00:30:20,6
I'm gonna talk
to Nick...

808
00:30:20,082 --> 00:30:22,1
Boring, boring,
boring, boring!

809
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:24,4
You don't decide who
gets punished and how.

810
00:30:24,061 --> 00:30:25,7
That's exactly what I do.

811
00:30:25,090 --> 00:30:27,2
No, no, you don't.

812
00:30:27,041 --> 00:30:29,2
This is how it
works, Lucifer.

813
00:30:34,025 --> 00:30:37,0
(sighs)

814
00:30:37,025 --> 00:30:39,1
Whatever speech
you have brewing, Maze,

815
00:30:39,033 --> 00:30:41,8
I don't want to hear it.

816
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:45,6
I think I've said
everything I need to.

817
00:30:47,084 --> 00:30:49,1
You're right.

818
00:30:49,039 --> 00:30:50,3
And I agree.

819
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:52,5
Let's go deliver
some punishment.

820
00:30:52,072 --> 00:30:53,5
(chuckles)

821
00:30:58,023 --> 00:31:00,5
We believe Josh may be
a very disturbed individual.

822
00:31:00,073 --> 00:31:02,2
(sighs)

823
00:31:02,044 --> 00:31:04,6
God.

824
00:31:04,090 --> 00:31:06,2
He caused all these?

825
00:31:06,049 --> 00:31:08,1
Yeah. All of them.

826
00:31:08,032 --> 00:31:10,7
I can't believe it. I...

827
00:31:10,095 --> 00:31:13,2
Tell me what really
happened, Nick.

828
00:31:13,041 --> 00:31:15,6
(sighs)

829
00:31:15,083 --> 00:31:19,2
I took Josh in
when he was 16.

830
00:31:19,042 --> 00:31:20,5
He was a runaway.

831
00:31:20,075 --> 00:31:23,7
He was a little broken.

832
00:31:23,096 --> 00:31:29,2
In him, I saw a little bit
of who I used to be.

833
00:31:29,047 --> 00:31:32,4
At least, I thought I did.

834
00:31:32,064 --> 00:31:34,2
So I took him under my wing.

835
00:31:34,047 --> 00:31:36,7
He was a natural.

836
00:31:36,098 --> 00:31:39,2
Taught him about all the lines
a pap can't cross.

837
00:31:39,048 --> 00:31:42,0
You know, 'cause I just...
I just wanted him to stop

838
00:31:42,023 --> 00:31:44,4
making the same mistakes
I did.

839
00:31:44,065 --> 00:31:45,4
Mm.

840
00:31:45,065 --> 00:31:47,4
And then, two days ago,

841
00:31:47,065 --> 00:31:50,0
he calls me up, says he's been
in a really bad accident,

842
00:31:50,024 --> 00:31:51,9
and said that
he totally understood

843
00:31:52,016 --> 00:31:54,3
everything I was saying now.

844
00:31:54,053 --> 00:31:56,2
But it was too late.

845
00:31:56,041 --> 00:31:58,2
You know, someone was dead.

846
00:31:58,045 --> 00:32:00,0
So you took the fall,

847
00:32:00,025 --> 00:32:02,9
hoping that Josh would get
a chance at a new life.

848
00:32:03,017 --> 00:32:04,7
Yeah.

849
00:32:04,092 --> 00:32:06,1
Nick Hofmeister finally tries to

850
00:32:06,038 --> 00:32:07,8
do something good with his life,

851
00:32:08,001 --> 00:32:10,2
and he gets played.

852
00:32:10,043 --> 00:32:12,4
You must really be
enjoying this.

853
00:32:12,064 --> 00:32:14,6
I'm really not.

854
00:32:14,089 --> 00:32:17,7
Believe it or not,
I forgive you.

855
00:32:17,097 --> 00:32:20,2
This isn't about you,
this isn't about me.

856
00:32:20,048 --> 00:32:22,0
This is about
Robbie Russell.

857
00:32:22,027 --> 00:32:24,9
You know, he was a kid who
didn't ask to be famous.

858
00:32:25,011 --> 00:32:27,3
He just wanted to
live a normal life.

859
00:32:30,032 --> 00:32:32,2
Nick, if you don't testify,
Josh will do this again.

860
00:32:34,070 --> 00:32:35,5
He'll do it again.

861
00:32:35,074 --> 00:32:37,9
(phone ringing)

862
00:32:38,020 --> 00:32:40,5
Excuse me.

863
00:32:40,075 --> 00:32:42,3
Oh. Just a second.

864
00:32:44,033 --> 00:32:45,4
Hey, Dan,
this better be important.

865
00:32:45,067 --> 00:32:47,1
I think Nick's about to talk.

866
00:32:47,038 --> 00:32:48,5
(sighs)

867
00:32:48,071 --> 00:32:51,4
No, I'm not following Josh. Why?

868
00:32:51,067 --> 00:32:53,7
What do you mean he's missing?

869
00:33:00,039 --> 00:33:02,2
Desk Sergeant?

870
00:33:02,048 --> 00:33:04,3
Yes, Detective?
Where did Nick Hofmeister go?

871
00:33:04,052 --> 00:33:05,6
Did somebody get him?

872
00:33:05,090 --> 00:33:07,3
Why, yes.

873
00:33:07,057 --> 00:33:09,4
It was that tall,
handsome British fella.

874
00:33:09,061 --> 00:33:11,4
Oh, no. I did it, too,

875
00:33:11,069 --> 00:33:13,1
didn't I?
(sighs)

876
00:33:21,004 --> 00:33:22,8
♪♪

877
00:33:35,043 --> 00:33:39,0
Oh, I respect what
you do, dung beetle.

878
00:33:39,026 --> 00:33:40,9
Much as celebrities hate you,

879
00:33:41,018 --> 00:33:44,6
you know, they need you,
keep them in the limelight.

880
00:33:44,081 --> 00:33:47,3
You're a...
a necessarily evil.

881
00:33:47,056 --> 00:33:49,3
Something I understand
all too well.

882
00:33:49,057 --> 00:33:51,7
But the-the trouble is
that you tried to change.

883
00:33:51,094 --> 00:33:52,9
Yeah?

884
00:33:53,011 --> 00:33:55,5
And you failed
spectacularly at it.

885
00:33:55,074 --> 00:33:59,5
Because, well,
sometimes we are what we are,

886
00:33:59,074 --> 00:34:01,7
and we should
embrace that.

887
00:34:04,041 --> 00:34:06,5
What are we doing
back here exactly?

888
00:34:06,079 --> 00:34:08,0
And do you need me to...?

889
00:34:08,025 --> 00:34:09,9
Maze!

890
00:34:10,017 --> 00:34:12,4
Did you bring me my gift?

891
00:34:14,097 --> 00:34:16,8
(grunting)

892
00:34:21,006 --> 00:34:22,0
(muffled panting)

893
00:34:27,027 --> 00:34:29,2
I'll kill you,
you crazy bitch.

894
00:34:30,044 --> 00:34:31,9
Just be polite to the lady.

895
00:34:32,019 --> 00:34:34,0
She isn't your enemy tonight.

896
00:34:36,011 --> 00:34:37,9
What is this?

897
00:34:38,016 --> 00:34:40,4
Right, well, both of you have
committed terrible acts

898
00:34:40,062 --> 00:34:41,7
worthy of punishment.

899
00:34:41,099 --> 00:34:42,9
However, you
will not receive

900
00:34:43,020 --> 00:34:44,4
said punishment
when you die.

901
00:34:44,066 --> 00:34:46,4
It's my fault, really. Sorry.

902
00:34:46,066 --> 00:34:48,2
So I'm here to fix that.

903
00:34:48,050 --> 00:34:49,9
Right now.

904
00:34:53,076 --> 00:34:55,5
Oh. Amateurs.

905
00:34:55,072 --> 00:34:57,0
All right, very well,
in terms you'll understand.

906
00:34:58,080 --> 00:35:00,6
You both get a gun.

907
00:35:00,085 --> 00:35:03,8
Let's see
who shoots who first.

908
00:35:11,048 --> 00:35:13,0
What's to stop us
from shooting you?

909
00:35:13,023 --> 00:35:15,3
Well, despite the waste
of bullets, let's see.

910
00:35:15,053 --> 00:35:17,4
He's about to rat you out
to the police.

911
00:35:19,032 --> 00:35:20,9
And he tricked you into
taking the fall for a murder

912
00:35:21,020 --> 00:35:22,2
he committed.
(chuckles)

913
00:35:22,049 --> 00:35:23,6
Discuss.

914
00:35:26,050 --> 00:35:28,3
You really did it, didn't you?

915
00:35:28,054 --> 00:35:30,0
You killed people.

916
00:35:32,050 --> 00:35:34,8
You lost your touch, Nick.

917
00:35:35,005 --> 00:35:37,7
All this talk about
lines we can't cross.

918
00:35:37,092 --> 00:35:39,9
Nowadays, the only way
to be first

919
00:35:40,018 --> 00:35:42,3
is to realize that
there is no line.

920
00:35:42,060 --> 00:35:44,3
And you were almost

921
00:35:44,056 --> 00:35:46,6
begging to take the fall.

922
00:35:46,089 --> 00:35:48,5
That one dramatic gesture.

923
00:35:48,077 --> 00:35:51,3
As if that would erase the fact
that you've been a piece of crap

924
00:35:51,056 --> 00:35:53,3
- for the last 30 years.
- You can't do this.

925
00:35:53,052 --> 00:35:55,4
I treated you
like a son.

926
00:35:56,057 --> 00:35:58,0
(gun clicks)

927
00:35:58,024 --> 00:35:59,5
(laughs)

928
00:35:59,074 --> 00:36:00,5
Oh, Maze,

929
00:36:00,078 --> 00:36:02,2
you fiend.

930
00:36:02,041 --> 00:36:04,0
Even I didn't see
that one coming.

931
00:36:04,028 --> 00:36:05,6
You really would've killed me.

932
00:36:13,021 --> 00:36:15,1
Nick...
(car approaching)

933
00:36:15,034 --> 00:36:17,5
I made a mistake, okay?
I realize that now.

934
00:36:17,076 --> 00:36:20,0
(car door opens)
And I'm sorry.
CHLOE: Stop!

935
00:36:20,022 --> 00:36:21,0
Don't shoot him!

936
00:36:22,018 --> 00:36:23,3
LUCIFER:
Detective,

937
00:36:23,059 --> 00:36:24,3
you're interrupting
my punishment.

938
00:36:24,060 --> 00:36:25,9
You, don't talk.

939
00:36:26,018 --> 00:36:27,4
You're lucky
I figured out your insane,

940
00:36:27,064 --> 00:36:28,6
ironic punishment
before anyone got killed.

941
00:36:28,081 --> 00:36:31,0
Nick, you tried
to do some good,

942
00:36:31,027 --> 00:36:32,9
to help someone.
Don't throw it all away.

943
00:36:33,010 --> 00:36:35,0
Nick, embrace
who you really are.

944
00:36:35,023 --> 00:36:36,7
Stop fighting it.
Come on.

945
00:36:36,098 --> 00:36:37,9
Don't listen to him, Nick.
You tried to change.

946
00:36:38,011 --> 00:36:39,1
Yeah.

947
00:36:40,036 --> 00:36:42,0
- And look what happened.
- Yeah.

948
00:36:42,020 --> 00:36:43,7
You screwed up,
but you know what? It's okay.

949
00:36:43,095 --> 00:36:45,1
You tried to change.
That's what's important.

950
00:36:45,037 --> 00:36:47,2
Humans.

951
00:36:47,045 --> 00:36:49,8
Fascinating, aren't they?

952
00:36:50,004 --> 00:36:52,0
Do you know,
perhaps they're onto something.

953
00:36:52,029 --> 00:36:54,3
Nick... don't.

954
00:37:09,077 --> 00:37:12,7
I was surprised
to hear from you, Lucifer.

955
00:37:12,098 --> 00:37:15,7
Well, not as surprised as I was.

956
00:37:15,098 --> 00:37:17,9
But I wanted to tell you
you were right.

957
00:37:18,015 --> 00:37:20,4
Hmm. Is that a joke?

958
00:37:20,069 --> 00:37:22,4
(chuckles)
No, I wish it were.

959
00:37:22,065 --> 00:37:25,2
But, no, you were right,
and I was wrong.

960
00:37:30,029 --> 00:37:31,2
So you'll return to Hell?

961
00:37:31,045 --> 00:37:33,1
What? No!

962
00:37:33,033 --> 00:37:35,0
That is absurd.

963
00:37:35,029 --> 00:37:37,1
No, you're right that
I've changed in my time here,

964
00:37:37,038 --> 00:37:39,0
and that I have absolutely
no control over it.

965
00:37:39,030 --> 00:37:41,8
And you know what?

966
00:37:45,047 --> 00:37:48,0
That feels positively thrilling.

967
00:37:49,051 --> 00:37:50,8
You asked me here
to tell me that?

968
00:37:51,010 --> 00:37:53,1
No, no, no,
I thought

969
00:37:53,031 --> 00:37:54,9
I'd use you to remedy a
situation that I've mishandled,

970
00:37:55,019 --> 00:37:57,6
and annoy you in the process.

971
00:37:57,086 --> 00:37:59,8
Kill two birds with one
prayer sort of thing, hmm?

972
00:38:00,007 --> 00:38:02,6
Luci...

973
00:38:02,082 --> 00:38:04,5
you should've taken the offer.

974
00:38:04,074 --> 00:38:07,1
Oh.

975
00:38:08,037 --> 00:38:10,2
(wings flapping)

976
00:38:15,050 --> 00:38:16,7
(groans)

977
00:38:17,033 --> 00:38:18,2
(gasps)

978
00:38:22,046 --> 00:38:24,8
You're looking
for someone?

979
00:38:25,001 --> 00:38:26,2
(gasps)

980
00:38:26,047 --> 00:38:29,0
But...

981
00:38:29,026 --> 00:38:30,8
you were just
over there.

982
00:38:31,006 --> 00:38:34,1
That's... that's
impossible.

983
00:38:40,040 --> 00:38:41,4
(indistinct
police radio chatter)

984
00:38:41,065 --> 00:38:43,4
(siren whoops)

985
00:38:52,024 --> 00:38:54,0
Yes?

986
00:38:54,020 --> 00:38:55,9
I saw Nick pull
the trigger.

987
00:38:56,016 --> 00:38:58,8
I heard the gunshot,
but Josh wasn't shot.

988
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:01,0
Did you put blanks
in the guns? Like...

989
00:39:01,029 --> 00:39:03,8
Was this some staged thing to
get a confession out of Josh?

990
00:39:04,001 --> 00:39:06,5
That's probably more plausible
to you than my angelic brother

991
00:39:06,076 --> 00:39:08,8
slowing time while I pluck
a bullet out of thin air,

992
00:39:09,001 --> 00:39:11,1
isn't it?

993
00:39:11,039 --> 00:39:13,6
Even with all that,

994
00:39:13,081 --> 00:39:15,9
you were standing
right in front of me.

995
00:39:16,018 --> 00:39:18,4
I blink, and you're here.

996
00:39:18,069 --> 00:39:20,1
Is there a question there,
Detective?

997
00:39:20,035 --> 00:39:22,3
You... (sighs)

998
00:39:22,052 --> 00:39:24,4
You know exactly
what I'm asking you.

999
00:39:24,069 --> 00:39:26,6
And you know exactly
what I'll answer.

1000
00:39:26,082 --> 00:39:29,6
You know, um...

1001
00:39:29,086 --> 00:39:32,7
it's quite fun,
this police malarkey, isn't it?

1002
00:39:34,066 --> 00:39:36,3
TRIXIE: Are we going
to watch a movie, Mommy?

1003
00:39:36,058 --> 00:39:38,6
CHLOE: No, babe, I just wanted
to talk to you about something.

1004
00:39:38,087 --> 00:39:41,8
So, before I was a cop,

1005
00:39:42,008 --> 00:39:43,6
I was an actress.

1006
00:39:43,088 --> 00:39:45,8
And I was in a movie.

1007
00:39:46,001 --> 00:39:48,8
And... it was this movie.

1008
00:39:49,005 --> 00:39:53,0
In the movie,
I do some very silly things.

1009
00:39:53,022 --> 00:39:55,1
Things that, uh,

1010
00:39:55,039 --> 00:39:57,7
maybe some of your friends
might tease you about.

1011
00:39:57,093 --> 00:40:00,8
But it is what it is,

1012
00:40:01,006 --> 00:40:03,3
and-and that's not me
anymore, okay?

1013
00:40:04,073 --> 00:40:06,1
(whispers):
I know.

1014
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:07,5
Hmm?

1015
00:40:07,078 --> 00:40:09,4
I've seen this
before, Mommy.

1016
00:40:09,070 --> 00:40:12,8
You have? Where?

1017
00:40:13,007 --> 00:40:15,8
I have the Internet.

1018
00:40:16,008 --> 00:40:17,3
Oh, right.

1019
00:40:17,058 --> 00:40:20,6
This isn't even in HD.

1020
00:40:20,083 --> 00:40:23,2
Mm. Hmm.

1021
00:40:24,079 --> 00:40:25,8
Well, what'd you think?

1022
00:40:26,009 --> 00:40:28,2
I thought it's hilarious!

1023
00:40:28,046 --> 00:40:30,2
You did?

1024
00:40:30,047 --> 00:40:32,5
My favorite part is when
you ate too much cake,

1025
00:40:32,076 --> 00:40:34,7
and then you puked in
that cute guy's hair.

1026
00:40:34,093 --> 00:40:36,1
(laughs)

1027
00:40:36,039 --> 00:40:38,0
That part is really funny.

1028
00:40:38,022 --> 00:40:42,0
Then you stop, and
we think it's all over.

1029
00:40:42,023 --> 00:40:43,0
Yeah.

1030
00:40:43,027 --> 00:40:45,2
But then...

1031
00:40:45,044 --> 00:40:46,8
- Blah! Blah!
- Oh.

1032
00:40:47,002 --> 00:40:49,3
(laughs)

1033
00:40:49,057 --> 00:40:50,5
Sorry, Mommy.

1034
00:40:50,078 --> 00:40:52,0
Didn't mean
to hurt you.

1035
00:40:52,028 --> 00:40:54,4
You didn't hurt me, baby.
I'm fine.

1036
00:40:54,066 --> 00:40:56,7
It's gonna get better soon.

1037
00:40:56,095 --> 00:40:59,7
I hope the guy who hurt you
got in lots of trouble.

1038
00:40:59,091 --> 00:41:02,7
You know,
I should go see him.

1039
00:41:02,092 --> 00:41:05,0
So, the Devil did
a good deed today.

1040
00:41:05,025 --> 00:41:06,5
(laughs):
Oh. Hmm.

1041
00:41:06,079 --> 00:41:08,7
- There's no need
to call it that.
- (chuckles)

1042
00:41:08,092 --> 00:41:10,4
I enjoyed
every minute of it.

1043
00:41:10,067 --> 00:41:13,6
(laughs)
You know what I mean.

1044
00:41:13,088 --> 00:41:15,8
Mm.

1045
00:41:16,001 --> 00:41:18,8
You know, I'm so very used to
being in control of everything.

1046
00:41:19,001 --> 00:41:22,1
Not knowing what's gonna
come next is...

1047
00:41:22,031 --> 00:41:23,9
Can be scary.

1048
00:41:24,015 --> 00:41:26,9
No. No, I'm finding it
quite exhilarating, actually.

1049
00:41:27,019 --> 00:41:28,4
- Hmm.
- (chuckles)

1050
00:41:28,069 --> 00:41:30,4
I think you were right,
by the way.

1051
00:41:30,061 --> 00:41:32,1
About what?

1052
00:41:32,036 --> 00:41:36,0
That it may be a "who"
that's changing me.

1053
00:41:36,024 --> 00:41:41,1
But now that begs the question:
what do I do with her?

1054
00:41:41,037 --> 00:41:43,1
WOMAN: I have to warn you,
he's heavily medicated.

1055
00:41:43,033 --> 00:41:46,4
I doubt he'll be able to string
two words together right now,

1056
00:41:46,067 --> 00:41:49,2
much less have
a conversation.

1057
00:41:49,042 --> 00:41:51,3
Thanks.

1058
00:41:54,013 --> 00:41:55,8
Hey, Jimmy.

1059
00:41:57,030 --> 00:41:59,3
So this is where
you ended up, huh?

1060
00:41:59,060 --> 00:42:02,1
I was so wrapped up in recovery,
I forgot to come visit.

1061
00:42:02,035 --> 00:42:04,9
You know, from when you shot me.

1062
00:42:08,061 --> 00:42:09,9
(sighs)

1063
00:42:10,019 --> 00:42:11,6
I have to ask you something,
Jimmy,

1064
00:42:11,090 --> 00:42:13,9
about that day.

1065
00:42:19,066 --> 00:42:21,6
What happened to you, Jimmy?

1066
00:42:21,087 --> 00:42:24,0
What happened
with Lucifer?

1067
00:42:26,067 --> 00:42:28,7
Lucifer?

1068
00:42:28,092 --> 00:42:30,8
What happened
when you shot at me?

1069
00:42:31,009 --> 00:42:32,8
- Is he here?!
Tell me he's not here!
- No.

1070
00:42:33,005 --> 00:42:34,5
No, Jimmy, he's not here.
He's not here, Jimmy.

1071
00:42:34,076 --> 00:42:36,3
I know he's here.

1072
00:42:36,051 --> 00:42:37,8
I can't get away.
I can't get away from him!

1073
00:42:39,055 --> 00:42:41,0
Jimmy, you're safe here.

1074
00:42:43,085 --> 00:42:45,1
(crying)
You're safe.

1075
00:42:45,031 --> 00:42:47,3
No, I'm not safe!
None of us are!

1076
00:42:47,056 --> 00:42:49,2
- He's just a man, Jimmy.
- You don't get it, do you?

1077
00:42:49,044 --> 00:42:52,1
He's the Devil!
He's the Devil!

1078
00:42:52,036 --> 00:42:53,5
He's the Devil!

1079
00:42:53,073 --> 00:42:56,3
He's the Devil! He's the Devil!

